Keyword and oneliner of the instrument as it left the House
MTR VEHICLE/OFFICE: Provides for a temporary waiver of fees for final delinquent debt
based on special circumstances
Report adopts Senate amendments to:
1. Change the emergency authority of the commissioner from temporarily waiving to
temporarily suspending any fine, fee, penalty, or license suspension appearing on a
person's driving record.
2. Remove the provision granting the commissioner full authority to reduce or eliminate
any obligation provided for in proposed law.
3. Provide for technical changes.
Report rejects Senate amendments which would have:
1. Added a proposed law provision suspending the hybrid vehicle road usage fee
provided for in present law (R.S. 32:461(A)(2)) until August 1, 2027 and provided
that failure to pay such fee would not be considered debt collectible under proposed
law or any other applicable collection authority.
2. Limited the suspension of the hybrid vehicle road usage fee to Mild Hybrid (MHEV)
and 48V Hybrid models.
Report amends the bill to:
1. Add a proposed law provision suspending the hybrid vehicle road usage fee provided
for in present law (R.S. 32:461(A)(2)) until August 1, 2027 for non-plugin hybrids
and to provide that failure to pay such fee cannot be considered debt that may be
collected pursuant to proposed law or any other applicable collection authority.
Digest of the bill as proposed by the Conference Committee
Present law (R.S. 32:8) allows the office of motor vehicles (OMV) to refer debts that are past
due 180 days and final for collection through the office of debt recovery, while notifying
debtors of payment options and possible fees. Authorizes the OMV to adopt rules for
referrals and, through the commissioner, compromise or settle debts to reduce collection
costs.
Proposed law retains present law but grants the commissioner of the OMV, or his designee,
emergency authority to temporarily suspend or place on hold, fees, penalties, or license
suspensions for up to 30 days to allow access to life-sustaining medicine or medical
treatment, with documentation from a healthcare provider.
Proposed law defines "commissioner" as the commissioner of the OMV for purposes of
proposed law.
